France and Germany have called for an end to Turkey’s assault against Syrian Kurdish forces in northeastern Syria. German Chancellor Angela Merkel visited French President Emmanuel Macron in Paris on Sunday to discuss developments in Syria. “We have a common desire that this offensive ends,” Macron stated, reiterating his warning that the continued Turkish offensive would create a humanitarian catastrophe as well as encourage the so-called Islamic State to return. Merkel, meanwhile, had earlier spoken to Turkey’s President Recep Tayyip Erdogan over the phone, calling for an immediate end to the military operation. Both France and Germany announced an end of arms exports to Turkey amid mounting international pressure. Read More at: